2016 has been pretty good to me in terms of traveling. Even though, I did not document my travels well, here are some pictures I clicked of the places I explored.

# Jim Corbett National Park
Known for its tigers, this National Park has unfortunately been heavily commercialized.  
I think I was not able to explore the park to its full potential. I certainly need to visit this place once more and explore more of its hidden sides.

# Roopkund
Roopkund trek is a high altitude trek in the Himalayas. The trail is breathtaking and diverse - from thick pine jungle, to lush green meadows, to rocky terrain with hardly any plants or trees. Recommended to anyone looking for quality adventure.

# Mcleodganj and Triund
Mcloadganj is a cozy little town in the Himalayas with a large Tibetan population. It is dotted with amazing cafes and people.
From Mcloadganj I hiked to a pretty well known and heavily visited hill station called Triund. The hike, though easy, is a pure joy to do solo.

# Delhi
